      "content": "The best approach is to ensure the texture is managed to look controlled and intentional, not messy. A sleek, defined style that showcases the texture while maintaining neatness is ideal, such as a well-defined twist-out or a sophisticated, structured updo. If the texture is allowed to be voluminous or loose, it needs to look deliberate, not like it was just rolled out of bed. Ultimately, the key is polish and structure, regardless of natural texture.",
